{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b62f93f5-cdda-4bfb-89dc-129d30802299","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **before** them. The `.fsproj` lists `Services.fs` before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFix: reorder the `<Compile>` items so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_H8ARFFl0npR5p4vw1vE7IJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bcf0a5b354a7463bb0a4c37639f868da/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bcf0a5b354a7463bb0a4c37639f868da/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"730a833e-df54-4461-9924-0acd9cff5c66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj` file:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compilation order, this will fail.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":500,"requestId":"042B:11B452:D54D9C:F36BD6:69F2A7EB"},"id":"4822c4e9-9b43-4f95-aa77-2ad82bf975ba","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:53:08.848Z","parentId":"6c2dfe45-de26-4385-af69-45a96c7d4e68"}
